The Akpanke Foundation (TAF) has donated palliatives to and paid over three million naira medical bills of the less privileged in Cross River State. The palliatives donated include thousands of facemasks, food stuff and other materials. The founder, Mr Peter Akpanke, while presenting the palliatives in Obudu Obanliku local governments of the state, yesterday, noted that the gesture was a thanksgiving to God Almighty, to mark his marriage anniversary and birthday celebrations during the week. Akpanke further said that the gift is to help the less privileged in the communities of Obudu and Obanliku local governments of the state. LEADERSHIP Sunday reports that 20 bikes were presented to youths including the 10 PDP ward chairmen of Obanliku and car gift to Mr Ben Ukukong of Ketting Bendi Obanliku during the occasion. The Thanksgiving Anniversary have in attended Prof. Sandy Ojong, RT Hon Legor Idagbo, RT. Hon. Jarigbe Agbom, Rt. Hon. Daniel Asuquo – (Dansuki), Rt. Hon. Eteng Jones , Barr Alphonsus Ogar Eba, Dr Steve Odey and a host of other dignitaries in attendance. “The Birthday Activities continued on Monday with the distribution of thousands of facemasks and other palliatives, visitation of hospitals to where his Foundation distributed food and paid medical bills surmounting to over 3million naira. “No doubt we could hear the people praising him with many lauding him as the Messiah God sent to bring succor and hope to the less privileged, he has touched the lives of people irrespective of family and tribe”.